NUMBER 376
NAME Palace, fountain
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A majestic bluestone dolphin stares somberly into the sky from the empty
fountain in the center of this grove. Gray branches rattle in a sharp gust of
wind. Fur-clad, a single sojourner paces beside the stone benches here, too
deep in meditation to notice the grove's stark beauty. A small path leads
, through the trees, to a somber building.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 375
ITEM 0 197 ADJ1=29 ADJ2=312
ITEM 1 339 ADJ1=312
ITEM 2 229
ITEM 3 80 VAL2=1050
;
NUMBER 1050
NAME Palace, mausoleum
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A white marble building, streaked with golden flecks, sits on top of a small
hill. Stone steps lead up to the arch which offers entrance to the building.
Brightly burning torches line the path, their illuminating glow fed by an
eternal magic. On either side of the arch is a beautiful golden statue,
standing guard over the young woman buried within with an eternal vigilance.
A silver plaque is set into the stone above the arch, flowing script
engraved into its surface. The branches of an ancient oak tree hang gently
over the building, almost cradling it within their leafy demesne. Thick
roots thrust from the ground and wend their way to the west forming the
edges of path.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1507
ITEM 0 376
ITEM 1 60 VAL2=1051
ITEM 2 346 ADJ1=468
ITEM 3 400 ADJ1=292
ITEM 4 229 ADJ1=216
ITEM 5 80 VAL2=376
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 3
    "May her brilliant light never dim, and be,"
    "eternally, a beacon for others to follow."
     May Rorin ever watch over you, daughter.

         Princess Solaria Kentaurus
                992-1018
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1507
NAME Palace, mausoleum
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Emerald green vines, bursting with beautiful roses of all hues, are draped
across the white marble mausoleum which sits in the middle of this clearing.
Broad steps, streaked with gold and silver flecks, lead up to a carved arch.
On either side of the arch a statue has been placed, the heads of the statues
bowed in reverence. The mighty roots of the barely visible oak tree to the
east protrude from the ground and join in front of the mausoleum to form
what look like a pair of cupped hands. Within the hands of the oak roots
burns a brilliant golden flame. The magnificent seal of the of the Kentaurus
family has been placed above the arch.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1050
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=347 ADJ2=187 VAL2=1508
ITEM 1 346
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The words, "Forever in our hearts, forever in our memories", are elegantly
scripted on the arch, flowing between the intricate carvings of leaves and
flowers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
This statue is the twin of the other one. Both are a depiction of a sorrowful
Shemri, her head bowed in prayer and her eyes filled with love and comfort.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 1508
NAME Inside Mausoleum
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Four marble sarcophagi rest upon the floor, each one with a carving atop
the lid. Golden braziers, each at one corner of the room, cast an eternal
light across the room, forcing all darkness far from this place.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 1507
ITEM 0 234 ADJ1=187
ITEM 1 234 ADJ1=187
ITEM 2 234 ADJ1=187
ITEM 3 234 ADJ1=187
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Artfully carved into the lid is a moving representation of King Frederick
Kentaurus the III. His eyes are closed and his hands are clasped on the
pommel of a brilliant greatsword. There is some writing at the top of the
sarcophagus.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
       "King Frederick Kentaurus the III"
                "956-1023"
