NUMBER 2270
NAME Underground
ASTRAL
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Hastily dug, this cramped tunnel, judging by its angle, seems to have had
its start deep below the earth. Any way of finding the tunnels start is
impossible, however, as it ends a little way to the south at an impassable
wall of rubble. Almost as if the diggers made sure that no one would be
able to find out where they came from. Strangely enough, the excavaters
went to a lot of trouble to bring a stone wall with them. The wall is
propped up against the the dirt wall to the east.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 2240
ITEM 2 420 ADJ1=312
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Crudely drawn paintings portray numerous drakin huddling meekly in front
large ant-like beings. In the next scene that ant-like beings are beheading
all of the drakins, until there are none left. The last scene has a large
death heads rune etched across one of ten symbols. The other nine are
vaguely familiar.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 => 1
    IFVAR RAC = 6
      ECHO PLAYER You are shocked to realize that the nine symbols that you can see on the wall represent the Drakin clans.
      ECHO OTHERS %N looks startled.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
