OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Park Avenue ends in front of an imposing stone wall. The majestic Royal Palace
of Fayd lies behind an iron gate. Two tough-looking members of the Royal Guard
inspect you from in front of the gate, while others keep a vigilant watch from
the ramparts above. The guards will brook no trouble, and no one without proof
of legitimate business may enter the grounds. The palace itself, what can be
seen of it through the gate, looks grand and is surrounded by extensive flower
beds and hedges. Recessed into the wall, to the left of the gate, is a large
polished mirmach door with a stylized desert rose artfully engraved into its
surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 273
