NUMBER 89
NAME Queen's Guard, headquarters
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Walls composed of stained wooden paneling surround this enormous chamber
in an aura of splendor. Thick wooden beams rise from floor to ceiling along
the walls of the chamber. Objects of martial glory, ranging from crossed
swords to colorful shields, hang from the front of the beams their presence
adding to the colorful atmosphere. Thick chains fall from the ceiling to
support a wooden chandelier that has large candles imbedded in it to serve
as the chamber's principal light source. Directly below the chandelier is
a magnificent oaken table, stained and then polished to a deep mahogany
lustre. High-backed wooden chairs, stained the same color as the table,
are carefully placed around the table in their proper positions. The
table and chairs have been placed upon a plush crismon rug with a beautiful
design sewn into its center. A gigantic fireplace crackles merrily from
the west end of the chamber, its flames casting off both heat and light.
Swaying gently in the heated air rising from the fireplace is a large
silken banner. The banner extends from the ceiling to the mantle of the
fireplace and has a blooming white desert rose beautifully sewn into its
center. A white marble arch leads back out to the hallway.
*DESCRIPTION_END
