ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Gracefully flowing sculptured benches rise from the worked stone
floor on either side of this long east-west hallway. Softly dazzling
light falls into the chamber from the intricate glass-stained ceiling to
highlight and accentuate the imposing statue that is the centerpiece of
the area. The statue stands taller than two men and fills the room with
its overpowering presence. An opening leads out into the street.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 27
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=312 VAL2=241
ITEM 1 346 ADJ1=178
EXTEND 1 of Ordanin
ITEM 2 339
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Twice the size of a normal man this statue is impressively carved to
portray the God of Justice. He is portrayed as being clad in golden armor
with a large sword held in his right hand and scales in his left. A large
pile of broken chains lies coiled at his feet and a large pouch, hung on
his belt, is tightly wrapped with more chains. Engraved at the base of
the statue is the name, "ORDANIN".
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Pleasantly comfortable the benches rise smoothly from the floor and wall
as if they had been carved from the same stone. A small plaque, set into
the floor before the benches reads, "Erected by Delanore, follower of
Ordanin."
*DESCRIPTION_END
VARIABLE mondelanore
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You glance out the opening, scanning the street...
   SHOWROOM 241
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The faint clicking noise caused by the slowly swaying scales builds quickly in your mind, until you begin to feel compelled to tell the truth, no matter the cost..
  ECHO OTHERS %N gazes, with awe, at the statue.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 8
    ADD mondelanore 1
